01682 /**

01686  * inbound message ports used by each SRIO MAC.  These channels are also
01687  * known as reassembly IDs (RIDs) on some of the other devices.  Care must
01688  * be taken to avoid using the same vport on more than one device.  The
01689  * 75xx default settings create a conflict that forces reprogramming this
01690  * register before message traffic can be enabled.  The typical 75xx vport
01691  * IDs allocations allow the SRIO MACS to use vports 6 thru 95.  The default
01692  * csr values allocate the following:
01693  *
